keyFacts: Travel voucher indicates government travel to Santa Monica, CA from December 15-18, 2019 for a witness interview related to the Epstein case.
The purpose field contains 'R20 - . . v. pstem - itnessInterview (California)' suggesting this is likely Department of Justice travel for investigative purposes.
The voucher total expenses were $2,227.40 with an estimated trip cost of $2,440.58.
The email was sent from the E2 Solutions government travel system to a DOJ email address on December 23, 2019.
The document shows ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of late 2019, several months after Epstein's death.
